The paper discusses Markov decision problems (MDPs), which are a fundamental concept in artificial intelligence (AI) research related to automated planning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI. The paper also discusses the running time of MDP solution algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions alternative methods of analysis that rely on the structure of MDPs, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
